item.title: Need help how to make your server Silabs
item.dc:creator: @crackheadKD crackheadKD
item.description:
@crackheadKD wrote:

The only difference between silab client and other clients is that silab has all the newer items available. Other then that, its just like every other client.
If your server has client-specific items (items that are only available/seen through 1 specific client) then you should remove them from the entire source.
All sources are already silab-compatible, as far as I know is that only the items are different in silabs.
I could be wrong.
